A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Municipalities – Enforcement Officers – Body–Worn Cameras
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing a municipality to adopt an ordinance or a resolution
4 authorizing an official who is authorized to act as an enforcement officer to utilize
5 body–worn cameras; requiring a municipality that adopts a certain ordinance or
6 resolution to publish a certain policy; and generally relating to enforcement officers
7 and body–worn cameras.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Local Government
10 Section 6–103.1
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2013 Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Local Government
16 6–103.1.
17 (A) A MUNICIPALITY MAY ADOPT AN ORDINANCE OR A RESOLUTION
18 AUTHORIZING AN OFFICIAL WHO IS AUTHORIZED TO ACT AS AN ENFORCEMENT
19 OFFICER TO UTILIZE A BODY–WORN CAMERA DURING THE COURSE OF THE
20 OFFICIAL’S DUTIES.
21 (B) A MUNICIPALITY THAT ADOPTS AN ORDINANCE OR A RESOLUTION
22 UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION SHALL DEVELOP AND PUBLISH A POLICY
23 FOR THE ISSUANCE AND USE OF A BODY–WORN CAMERA BY AN ENFORCEMENT
24 OFFICER THAT ADDRESSES:
